description: ADHD, Autistic, Artist. Photography + Video Creation. Camera Enthusiasts, Audiophile, Lover of Tech.
tweet: @codywanner @Ajc_Tm I‚Äôve always been able to do what I need to do. But life has felt VERY hard. Everything is an uphill battle. This extra effort lead to a constant feeling of burnout and depression. That‚Äôs why I decided to try medication. Would rather not take it if I could.

name: Stephen Jones
description: ADHD, Autistic, Artist. Photography + Video Creation. Camera Enthusiasts, Audiophile, Lover of Tech.
tweet: @Ajc_Tm @codywanner That all being said, once those 12 hours are up I‚Äôm back to useless. Everything feels hard again, and I‚Äôm back to baseline.  (Might look into a very small dose of something short acting for after work).

name: Stephen Jones
description: ADHD, Autistic, Artist. Photography + Video Creation. Camera Enthusiasts, Audiophile, Lover of Tech.
tweet: @Ajc_Tm @codywanner Normally after work I‚Äôm so worn out I can‚Äôt do anything. I find everything takes so much mental effort that being with people just makes it worse. Medicated I feel I could go out and do things, I feel more inclined to take my wife on a date.

name: Stephen Jones
description: ADHD, Autistic, Artist. Photography + Video Creation. Camera Enthusiasts, Audiophile, Lover of Tech.
tweet: @Ajc_Tm @codywanner So Lisdexamfetamine, Vyvanse 20mg. Very small dose, and it slowly releases over a 12-14h period. With such a small amount I do not see any negatives. I feel more capable of social and in person interaction taking it. I normally feel quite introverted.
